# Design System

### Color Palette (WhatsApp Theme)
All colors are defined as CSS variables in `globals.css` and exposed via Tailwind's `@theme` directive.

```css
/* Primary WhatsApp Colors */
--whatsapp-dark-teal: #075e54;   /* Primary brand, sidebar bg, headings */
--whatsapp-teal: #128c7e;        /* Secondary brand, borders */
--whatsapp-green: #25d366;       /* Active states, CTAs, success */
--whatsapp-light-green: #dcf8c6; /* Badges, highlights, soft backgrounds */
--whatsapp-beige: #ece5dd;       /* Page background, hover states */

/* Status Colors */
--red: #ff483a;                  /* Urgent, errors, critical deadlines */
/* Amber: use Tailwind's amber-500 */
```

**Tailwind Usage:**
- `bg-whatsapp-dark-teal` - Sidebar background
- `bg-whatsapp-green` - Active nav items, primary buttons
- `bg-whatsapp-light-green` - Badges, soft highlights
- `bg-whatsapp-beige` - Page background, hover states
- `text-whatsapp-dark-teal` - Primary headings
- `text-whatsapp-light-green` - Sidebar text

### Typography

**Font Family:** Ubuntu, Helvetica, sans-serif (set on body)

| Element | Classes |
|---------|---------|
| Page Title | `text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-whatsapp-dark-teal` |
| Section Header | `text-sm font-semibold tracking-wide text-whatsapp-dark-teal uppercase` |
